<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-60-0186 </DOCNO><TEXT>A case is presented for a revival in the development of small scale (500- 10,000 kW) hydroelectric installations in the United Kingdom. Methodsbased on larger scale projects involving many teams of high-cost specialistsare inappropriate in this power range. Small hydropower exploitationis best achieved through specialist equipment manufacturers offeringfull turnkey services. A brief outline is given of the services offeredby a water engineering company employing a multiskill team. Attentionis drawn to the investment criteria, costs, taxes and charges in theUK which have an adverse effect on the development of this non-polluting,renewable source of energy. (U.K.).</TEXT></DOC>